AD_FIELD.NAME: Module
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the module the element forms part of.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Change Version
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Change the selected dependency version to any version available in the module management window
AD_FIELD.HELP: * This button will trigger a dropdown menu displaying available versions for the selected dependency. * Display a warning to inform the user about potential downgrade issues. * Clearly mark any dependencies that need to be added or removed with tags like "New Dependency" or "Updated". * If incompatible, show a warning message to alert the user.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Client
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Active
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Organization
AD_FIELD.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Uninstall Dependency
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Uninstall the selected dependency from the environment
AD_FIELD.HELP: Depending on the dependency format, the uninstallation will vary: * Dependency in JAR format: the process will simply delete the dependency register. * Dependency in Source format (downloaded from Module Management window or Local): apart from deleting the dependency, the process will also erase the dependency source folders from the environment. This process only deletes the selected module, not its dependencies.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Version Status
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The Version Status Selector is a component of the Dependency Management module, designed to quickly inform users about the status of their software dependencies
AD_FIELD.HELP: Has 3 (three) states: - Update Available: Newer version available. Consider updating for improvements. - Updated: Dependency is at its latest version. No action needed. - Deprecated: May be outdated or unsupported.
